weather_summary: On January 1, 2012, the weather was characterized by a light drizzle, though no precipitation accumulation was recorded. The maximum temperature reached 12.8°C, while the minimum temperature dropped to 5.0°C, indicating a mild winter day. Wind conditions were gentle with speeds of 4.7 km/h, contributing to the overall moderate weather.

On January 2, 2012, the weather was characterized by significant rainfall, with total precipitation measuring 10.9 mm. The temperature fluctuated between a maximum of 10.6°C and a minimum of 2.8°C, indicating a relatively mild day overall. Winds were present at a speed of 4.5 km/h, contributing to the damp conditions. Overall, the day was marked by rainy weather, impacting outdoor activities and the general atmosphere.

On January 3, 2012, the weather was characterized by rainfall, with a total precipitation of 0.8 mm. The temperatures ranged from a minimum of 7.2°C to a maximum of 11.7°C, offering a relatively mild winter day. Wind speeds were recorded at 2.3 m/s, contributing to a damp atmosphere. Overall, the day was marked by wet conditions, typical of winter weather, with persistent rain being the predominant feature.

On January 4, 2012, the weather was characterized by significant rainfall, totaling 20.3 millimeters. The day experienced mild temperatures with a maximum of 12.2°C and a minimum of 5.6°C, indicating a relatively cool atmosphere. Wind speeds reached 4.7 km/h, contributing to the overall chilly feel of the day. The predominant weather condition was rainy, which may have influenced outdoor activities and travel plans in the area.

On January 5, 2012, the weather reflected a rainy day with a total precipitation of 1.3 mm. Temperatures ranged from a minimum of 2.8°C to a maximum of 8.9°C, indicating a cool atmosphere overall. Wind conditions were moderate, recorded at 6.1 km/h, contributing to the chilly feel of the day. This combination of factors created a damp and cool environment, typical of a winter day characterized by rain.
